When we were unable to determine the DALYs, we referred to a pathology that was clinically similar to our complication (e.g., respiratory failure or other severe cardiovascular diseases). The durations of short-term complications were taken from the literature review of Jha’s article [18]. The DALY calculation was then applied to all the stays of our population.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
